cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.CE 

The paper focuses on developing an architecture for explainable modeling of tabular data using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the use of graph representations, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper proposes an augmented model training approach, which could be categorized under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
